<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5109] Wrong path matching for http whiteboard service</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5109</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems we have some bugs in the path matching which result from different handling between the http service and the servlet spec. &lt;br/&gt;
For the http service, an alias like &quot;/foo&quot; matches &quot;/foo&quot; and &quot;/foo/*&quot; - while for the servlet spec &quot;/foo&quot; only matches &quot;/foo&quot; - exact match.&lt;br/&gt;
Right now, in both cases &quot;/foo/*&quot; matches.&lt;br/&gt;
For the servlet spec a pattern like &quot;/foo/*&quot; matches &quot;/foo/something&quot; but also &quot;/foo&quot;. Right now we don&apos;t handle the second case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
